snippet.title: Johnny Depp denies inflicting huge bruise on Amber Heard shown in court
snippet.description: denied inflicting a huge bruise on Amber Heard when he appeared in court yesterday.  The Pirates Of The Caribbean actor was shown a picture of this ex-wife's arm with the bruise, but said he was not responsible for the injury.   He was giving evidence at London's High Court in the second day of his libel trial against News Group Newspapers (NGN), and its executive editor Dan Wootton over an April 201 article which labelled him a "wife beater" - an egation he strenuously denies.   Sasha Wass QC, for NGN, said Ms Heard had started photographing her injuries so she could show him what he had done later.   Depp said he had never seen the photo before, so if that was her motive it had not happened.  "I didn't hit Ms Heard and furthermore I have never hit Ms Heard," he said.  Depp has denied  claims he was ever violent towards his ex-wife.   He in turn has accused Heard of abuse during the marriage, which she denies.  Depp returned to the witness box on Wednesday for the second day giving  ...
